# Security invariants (clinic-crm)

This is a multi-tenant medical CRM under India DPDP. Treat patient data as PHI.

## Non-negotiable

- **Every new tenant-scoped table MUST carry a `clinic_id` column AND have an
  RLS policy + audit trigger added in the same Alembic migration.** Use the
  `.cursor/skills/add-tenant-table/SKILL.md` checklist.
- **Never query a tenant table without an RLS context set.** The API runs
  `SET LOCAL app.current_user_id = ...` before any business logic. If you find
  yourself reaching for `row_security = off` outside of seed/migration code,
  stop — you're doing it wrong.
- **Never log PHI.** `phone`, `address`, `allergies`, `medical_history`, `dob`,
  full names and emails of patients must be stripped before any logger call.
  The PII redactor in `app/core/logging.py` is a safety net, not a license.
- **Encrypted columns** (`*_enc`) hold `pgp_sym_encrypt` output. Always
  decrypt at the edge of the service layer and never write a plaintext PHI
  column.
- **Audit every mutation.** Triggers cover insert/update/delete on patients,
  visits, prescriptions, media, shares. App code also emits explicit audit
  rows for login, login_failed, exports, share creation/revocation, and
  external share unlocks.
- **No PHI in URLs.** Use ids only. Patient codes (`DC-2026-00001`) are not
  PHI but should still not appear in third-party tracker URLs.
- **TLS only.** HSTS + CSP are set in `infra/docker/nginx.conf`. Don't loosen.

## Code smells that trigger a hard NO

```python
# ❌ logging PHI
logger.info("patient phone", phone=patient.phone)

# ❌ bypassing RLS to "just get this working"
await session.execute(text("SET LOCAL row_security = off;"))
await session.execute(select(Patient))

# ❌ storing plaintext PHI
session.add(Patient(phone="+91-..."))
```

```python
# ✅ logging with safe identifiers only
logger.info("patient_created", patient_id=patient.id, clinic_id=patient.clinic_id)

# ✅ RLS context first, then ordinary ORM/SQL
await set_rls_context(session, user_id=principal.user_id)
patients = await session.execute(select(Patient))

# ✅ encrypted column write
text("INSERT INTO patients (..., phone_enc) VALUES (..., pgp_sym_encrypt(:phone, :key))")
```
